OL,3,C'Top secret' surprise for D-Day
OL,4,Cveteran celebrating 100th birthday
OL,6,FA veteran of the D-Day landings has
OL,7,Fcelebrated his 100th birthday with a
OL,8,F"top secret" surprise at his care home
OL,9,Fin Somerset.
OL,11,FLieutenant Richard Willis RN was the
OL,12,Fsecond in command on a landing craft
OL,13,Ftasked with taking US tanks and troops
OL,14,Fto Utah beach in Normandy as part of
OL,15,FOperation Overlord in June 1944.
OL,17,FHe was wounded in the leg by shrapnel
OL,18,Fduring the attack and many years later
OL,19,Fwas awarded the Legion d'Honneur by
OL,20,Fthe French government.
