OL,3,C'Top secret' surprise for D-Day
OL,4,Cveteran celebrating 100th birthday
OL,6,FThe chart ` once labelled Top Secret `
OL,7,Fwas inscribed: "Presented to Lt
OL,8,FRichard Willis... on the occasion of
OL,9,Fhis 100th birthday. With the thanks
OL,10,Fand admiration of the Lord-Lieutenant
OL,11,Fand the people of Somerset."
OL,13,FIt was presented by Rear Admiral Peter
OL,14,FSparkes, chief executive of the UK
OL,15,FHydrographic Office, who said:
OL,16,F"Landings on to opposed beaches are
OL,17,Famongst the most dangerous combat
OL,18,Fexperiences in any conflict.
