OL,3,C'Top secret' surprise for D-Day
OL,4,Cveteran celebrating 100th birthday
OL,6,F"The fact that D-Day landings were
OL,7,Fsuccessful changed the course of the
OL,8,FSecond World War.
OL,10,F"The sacrifices made in those days
OL,11,Fshould never be forgotten. To honour
OL,12,Fone of our local veterans in this way
OL,13,Fis really the least we could do."
OL,15,FLt Willis, who was joined by his
OL,16,Ffamily for the surprise, said: "I'm
OL,17,Fnot sure what I've done to deserve
OL,18,Fthis.
OL,20,F"I was just there. But D-Day was an
OL,21,Fexperience I will never forget."
